        <updateDate>2016-08-05T14:25:58Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Safe Harbor for Reporting Violent Behavior Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill makes an employer immune from civil liability for reporting to a potential future employer an employee or former employee&rsquo;s violent or threatening behavior. The report must be made in good faith and based on objectively reasonable suspicion.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill makes a potential employer immune from civil liability for taking a reasonable action in good faith to respond to a report of violent or threatening behavior of an employee or potential employee.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
